description: Seedz Certified Organic Seeds are grown, harvested, packed, and shipped by hand right here in the USA. Our heirloom seeds are USDA Organic and Verified Non GMO. We believe in healthy environments, healthy communities, and healthy bodies. That’s why we take such care to ensure that all of our heirloom vegetable seeds are of the highest possible quality available.
ABOUT YOUR NEW ORGANIC LETTUCE SEEDS

The Seedz Parris Island Cos Lettuce Seeds are cool-season annuals that produce a fast-growing, multipurpose lettuce for baby leaf and full-size heads. Baby leaves size up quickly for salad mixes while the upright, uniform grey-green heads have nicely savoyed leaves.
For best results, direct-seed Spring to Fall or start transplants at 50-75°F 4 weeks before planting out.
Plant seeds 1/8” deep at 3 seeds per foot with 12-18” between rows. Seeds may take 21-28 days to germinate, 28 days to baby, 55 days to full maturity.
HOW TO USE YOUR HEIRLOOM LETTUCE SEEDS
Once fully grown and harvested, Parris Island Cos Lettuce is the perfect addition to any salad mix, sandwich, or wrap.
